    "actor_description": "Something heavy drops into my stomach like a stone finding water. My thoughts keep running a few steps ahead, rehearsing what could go wrong, and every option tastes metallic. I can still move and talk, but it feels like I'm doing it under a low ceiling. I keep listening for the moment the other shoe finally hits.",
    "description_text": "{actor} grows quieter and more deliberate, as if weighing each second. Their gaze drifts into middle distance; their jaw sets and releases, and their breathing turns measured, careful. They don't look panicked-just like they're bracing for bad news that hasn't arrived yet.",
    "alternate_descriptions": {
        "auditory": "Their voice comes out lower and tighter, with longer pauses-words chosen like they might matter later. You catch a slow inhale that stops halfway, then finishes as a controlled exhale.",
